<% count = @accesses.count %>
<% this = (count > 1) ? "These" : "This" # According to Rails, the singular of 'this' is 'thare'. %>
<% target_display_login = "#{@target.display_login}" %>
Hey <%= @user.display_login %>,

<%= target_display_login %> access has been approved on the following fine-grained personal access tokens:
An administrator in the <%= target_display_login %> organization has approved access on your fine-grained personal access <%= "token".pluralize(count) %>.

<%= "#{this} token".pluralize(count) %> can be used to access resources inside the <%= "@#{target_display_login}" %> organization.

<% @accesses.each do |access| %>
  - <%= access.name %>
<% end %>

If you run into problems, please contact support by visiting <%= contact_url %>

Thanks,
The GitHub Team
